  "response_text": "# Complete Fitness & Diet Plan for Overall Wellness\n\n## FITNESS PLAN (5-6 days/week)\n\n### Weekly Structure\n- **2-3 days**: Strength training (30-45 min)\n- **2-3 days**: Cardio (20-30 min)\n- **Daily**: Flexibility/mobility work (10-15 min)\n- **1 day**: Complete rest\n\n### Strength Training\n- Full-body workouts or upper/lower split\n- Focus: Compound movements (squats, deadlifts, bench press, rows)\n- 8-12 reps, 3-4 sets per exercise\n- Rest 48 hours between intense sessions\n\n### Cardio Options\n- Walking, running, cycling, swimming\n- Mix steady-state with interval training\n- Start with 150 min/week moderate intensity\n\n### Flexibility\n- Stretching, yoga, or foam rolling\n- Post-workout or separate sessions\n\n---\n\n## NUTRITION PLAN\n\n### Daily Macros (adjust to goals)\n- **Protein**: 0.8-1g per lb bodyweight\n- **Carbs**: 40-50% of calories\n- **Fats**: 25-35% of calories\n\n### Meal Framework (3 meals + 1-2 snacks)\n\n**Breakfast**\n- Eggs, oatmeal, berries, Greek yogurt\n\n**Lunch**\n- Lean protein + whole grains + vegetables\n\n**Dinner**\n- Fish/chicken + sweet potato + greens\n\n**Snacks**\n- Nuts, fruit, protein shake, cottage cheese\n\n### Key Principles\n✓ Whole, minimally processed foods  \n✓ Plenty of vegetables & fruits  \n✓ Adequate hydration (8+ glasses water)  \n✓ Consistent meal timing  \n✓ Limit added sugars & ultra-processed foods  \n✓ Plan meals ahead\n\n---\n\n## RECOVERY & LIFESTYLE\n\n- **Sleep**: 7-9 hours nightly\n- **Stress**: Meditation, deep breathing\n- **Hydration**: ½ body weight in ounces daily\n- **Consistency**: More important than perfection\n\n**Start here and adjust based on progress and how you feel.**",
